Name: Titus Parrilla
Review Text: The food was very delicious but had to wait quite some time for the it. They brought the soup and the steak together, so my steak got a little cold while eating the soup. The service was very kind and helpful and the toilets were also neat.

Name: Titus Parrilla
Review Text: There are several steakhouses doing cheap tourist menus in Amsterdam and my boring friends decided to basically have the same food every single night. This was the best, at least food-wise. The pepper steak was surprisingly good, really excellent for the price. The staff was friendly and they have heaters outside

Name: Titus Parrilla
Review Text: Stopped here for breakfast one morning. Nice speedy service and friendly waitress. Toilets are at the back up the stairs. The food was fine and so was the coffee. Nice location to sit and watch the world go past in rembrant square.

Name: Titus Parrilla
Review Text: Horrible restaurant. A must avoid. Hopeless service. Took 1.5 hours for the food to come. Taste was just ok. They don't accept pin. You can only pay by cash. Would not go back if someone would pay me to!

Name: Titus Parrilla
Review Text: A nicely located restaurant in a busy yet chilled area. The food was quite a disaster. My friend's steak came cold and my Caesar salad was totally off. I never experienced a Caesar salad with arugula, tomatoes & cucumbers, and no Parmesan. The dressing was a ready made one instead of the one made from scratch. Too bad!
